          "text": "The user is asking why a page fault would occur on a committed but not yet accessed page. They're confused because they think page fault means \"accessing an address that doesn't exist in RAM\", but they're right that the process hasn't accessed it yet. Let me clarify the sequence of events.\n\nActually, I need to re-read what I said. I said \"commit сделан, но страница не вызвана → page fault будет при первом чтении\". This is actually correct - when the process *first* reads/writes to that committed address, a page fault occurs because the OS allocated the virtual address but hasn't yet mapped a physical page to it. The page fault is what *triggers* the OS to map a physical page.\n\nBut the user is confused because they think page fault = error/bad thing. They're right that the process is accessing a valid committed address - it's just that the physical page hasn't been allocated yet. Let me explain this more clearly.",
